title: Pointed space
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A //pointed space// $$(X,x)$$ is a topological space $$X$$ together with a point $$x \in X.$$ A morphism of pointed spaces is a continuous map $$f\colon (X,x) \to (Y,y)$$ such that $$f(x) = y.$$